        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-1737",
        "content": "When he thought of it Dan felt as if he could not wait, but must burst that narrow cell and fly away, as the caddis worms he used to watch by the brookside shed their stony coffins, to climb the ferns and soar into the sky.",
        "style_prompt": "F_p-normal_s-normal_e-normal",
        "gender": "F",
